{"source_key":"sha256-c8597aca71664a84bdd657ea13dadbd3","record_index":1182,"record_hash":"sha256:f4210ccdfc098aa8310f0a92d7c2dda5bf12ec73910ed6bcd1e202238f419ac2","timestamp":"2026-05-20T02:25:21.535Z","kind":"tool_call","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:custom_tool_call","role":null,"text":null,"tool_name":"apply_patch","tool_input":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Update File: /Users/kiril/Documents/tars/Tars/02 [REDACTED:entropy].md\n@@\n-Turn identity should be derived from capture content, not from time or provider\n-turn ids. Use a 128-bit truncated SHA-256 value: take the first 16 bytes of the\n-digest and render them as 32 lowercase hex characters.\n+Turn identity should be derived from capture content, not from time or provider\n+turn ids. Use a 128-bit truncated SHA-256 value: take the first 16 bytes of the\n+digest and render them as 32 lowercase hex characters.\n+\n+Key formats:\n+\n+- session, source, and turn keys: `sha256-<32 lowercase hex chars>`\n+- transcript record hashes: `sha256:<full lowercase hex digest>`\n+\n+The turn-key digest input is the canonical stored strings encoded as UTF-8, with\n+a NUL byte between every component:\n \n ```text\n-turn-key = sha256-trunc128(session_key + NUL + source_key + NUL + ordered_new_record_hashes)\n+session_key NUL source_key NUL record_hash_1 NUL record_hash_2 NUL ...\n ```\n \n+There is no empty-record case because a capture turn is only created after at\n+least one new transcript record is accepted.\n+\n That makes the newly accepted transcript records the identity of what this\n capture observed. Capture timestamp and environment snapshot are turn\n attributes, not identity. This also makes retries easier: the same accepted\n record set maps to the same turn key.\n@@\n The record membership matters because `but-agentlog` already deduplicates\n records. Without turn membership, repeated hook capture preserves the transcript\n but erases the boundaries between capture invocations.\n+\n+`TurnDetail.records` must be an ordered array. That order is authoritative for\n+rendering records within a capture turn; hashes and source indexes identify the\n+records, but they are not a replacement for sequence.\n@@\n Capture should also have a simple concurrency rule. Either hold a repo/session\n capture lock around dedupe, previous-turn lookup, and write, or use optimistic\n retry if the record-hash set or latest turn summary changes before the atomic\n write. `previous_turn_key` means \"the latest committed capture turn in this\n session immediately before this turn was written.\"\n+\n+If an environment snapshot is written as `partial` or `failed`, a later retry may\n+enrich that existing turn instead of creating a transcriptless turn. The\n+enrichment must only update environment data and derived index entries for the\n+same capture turn, and should use the same atomic `apply_edits` path.\n@@\n one `apply_edits` call for transcript appends, record hash updates, turn detail\n writes, turn summary appends, and index updates.\n+The capture path should not use plain `set`, `set_record`, or similar\n+out-of-band writes for session/source metadata once turn writes are introduced.\n*** End Patch\n","source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T02:25:21.535Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"custom_tool_call","status":"completed","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]","name":"apply_patch"}}}